1221
01:30:56.000 --> 01:30:58.000
I do this repeatedly.

1222
01:30:58.000 --> 01:31:02.000
Enough that we decide I can no longer go through the selection process at all.

1223
01:31:02.000 --> 01:31:04.000
I will be caught sneaking away from the line and shot.

1224
01:31:04.000 --> 01:31:06.000
There has to be another way.

1225
01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:09.000
We have to get out of here and repeat over and over in my mind.

1226
01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:12.000
I know we cannot give up because I have hope.

1227
01:31:12.000 --> 01:31:14.000
I always remember what my father told me.

1228
01:31:14.000 --> 01:31:17.000
Stay together because your chances of survival will be much better.

1229
01:31:17.000 --> 01:31:20.000
It is not easy to keep hope alive when we are in camp.

1230
01:31:20.000 --> 01:31:22.000
Giving up seems easier.

1231
01:31:22.000 --> 01:31:27.000
And we see many who do give up and end up on the electric fencing.

1232
01:31:27.000 --> 01:31:30.000
There are a few good rumors that help us have hope.

1233
01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:35.000
Women gather in the bathroom to hear the latest rumor that the Americans or Russians may liberate us.

1234
01:31:35.000 --> 01:31:39.000
The hope that we will reunite with Tata and Fiscal keeps us alive.

1235
01:31:39.000 --> 01:31:42.000
Even with this hope it is hard to continue believing in something.

1236
01:31:42.000 --> 01:31:44.000
We all question our faith in God.

1237
01:31:44.000 --> 01:31:47.000
