1262
01:32:48.000 --> 01:32:51.000
The female capo guarding the door raises her hand to stop me.

1263
01:32:51.000 --> 01:32:54.000
My heart is beating hard in my chest as she looks at me.

1264
01:32:54.000 --> 01:32:56.000
You can't go out this door.

1265
01:32:56.000 --> 01:32:58.000
You have to go out that way to be selected for work.

1266
01:32:58.000 --> 01:33:00.000
She says pointing in the opposite direction.

1267
01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:01.000
I don't want to go to work.

1268
01:33:01.000 --> 01:33:02.000
I say shaking my head.

1269
01:33:02.000 --> 01:33:05.000
My mother has just gone out that door and I need to go with her.

1270
01:33:05.000 --> 01:33:07.000
As I point to the door behind her.

1271
01:33:07.000 --> 01:33:08.000
The second's pass.

1272
01:33:08.000 --> 01:33:10.000
The second's that pass before she responds.

1273
01:33:10.000 --> 01:33:12.000
Feel like hours.

1274
01:33:12.000 --> 01:33:14.000
I continue to reach toward the door.

1275
01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:16.000
Employing her to help me.

1276
01:33:16.000 --> 01:33:20.000
Somehow the capo takes pity on me and lets me out the door.

1277
01:33:20.000 --> 01:33:24.000
I scan the area for guards as I sneak around the building to join my sisters in line.

1278
01:33:24.000 --> 01:33:27.000
There are enough people moving about that no one sees me enter the group.

1279
01:33:27.000 --> 01:33:30.000
I can see my sisters and they have a spot for me to slide into.

1280
01:33:30.000 --> 01:33:33.000
I feel a sense of freedom for the first time in a long time.

1281
01:33:33.000 --> 01:33:35.000
Suddenly I know I am strong and brave.

1282
01:33:35.000 --> 01:33:38.000
It is as though an angel is looking after me.

1283
01:33:38.000 --> 01:33:42.000
I think as I look upward, maybe it's my mother who helps me out of this terrible situation.

1284
01:33:42.000 --> 01:33:44.000
Maybe things will get better for us now.

1285
01:33:44.000 --> 01:33:46.000
I make eye contact with how you saw her.

